<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-10-07T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-10-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="609" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.51/191: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-10-07T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 7,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>50. Your 71, September 23, 2 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Cumberland has given draft of contract to Peruvian Ambassador who has
                            cabled the important features to his Government and has requested
                            instructions. If the contract is approved, discreetly suggest to the
                            President that the Ambassador be authorized to sign immediately.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>